# Pythia - Website Performance Analyzer

A comprehensive website analysis tool that provides 10 specialized metrics plus a unified P-Score.

## Metrics

1. **Karpov Speed** (25% weight) - Page load performance
2. **Vortex Access** (15% weight) - Accessibility score
3. **Nova Scale** (12% weight) - Infrastructure & CDN
4. **Aether Tech** (10% weight) - Modern web technologies
5. **Pulse SEO** (10% weight) - Search & social optimization
6. **Eden Efficiency** (8% weight) - Page weight & resource efficiency
7. **Helix Privacy** (8% weight) - Security headers & tracking
8. **Echo Green** (7% weight) - Sustainable hosting
9. **Quantum Quality** (3% weight) - Code best practices
10. **Nexus Mobile** (2% weight) - Mobile responsiveness

## P-Score

Unified performance score (0-100) combining all metrics with intelligent weighting based on real-world priorities.

## Deploy to Vercel via GitHub

1. Create new GitHub repository
2. Add all files (api/scan.js, index.html, package.json, vercel.json, .gitignore)
3. Push to GitHub
4. Go to vercel.com/new
5. Import your GitHub repository
6. Deploy (Vercel auto-detects everything)

No terminal commands required!

## Local Development

If you want to test locally:
```
npm install -g vercel
vercel dev
```

But for production, just use GitHub â†’ Vercel dashboard deployment.
